div1.p:
260.
GEORGE THOMAS BODMAN (26)
PLEADED GUILTY
to stealing, on January 20th, 1897, thirteen miniatures and other articles;
also, on December 12th, 1900, a gold scarf pin;
also, on October 5th, 1902, a parcel of watches and a pair of Kruger sleeve links;
also, in 1904, a quantity of postage stamps;
also, on December 3rd, 1903, a pair of dividers, the property of
David Martin Currie.
Judgment respited.
